<subSubSection pageId="231" pageNumber="509" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="231.[1991,2586,1763,2181]" pageId="231" pageNumber="509">
<taxonomicName box="[1992,2112,1876,1905]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Abrothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="231" pageNumber="509" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Abrothrix</taxonomicName>
manniis in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[2466,2586,1876,1905]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Abrothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="231" pageNumber="509" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Abrothrix</taxonomicName>
and was removed from the former concept of A. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Osgood" baseAuthorityYear="1943" box="[2072,2183,1960,1985]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Abrothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="231" pageNumber="509" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sanborni">sanborni</taxonomicName>
, mostly based on molecular grounds. Therefore, part of the data available in the literature for A. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Osgood" baseAuthorityYear="1943" box="[2375,2486,2030,2063]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Abrothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="231" pageNumber="509" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sanborni">sanborni</taxonomicName>
relates to A. mann. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
